Adhoc commands:
Single line commands.
Perform quick tasks without creating playbooks.

Why?
	1. Test connectivity of ansible server/ check communication 
Between ansible & host servers.
	2. Check free/ disk space.
	3. Restart services.
	4. Check uptime.
	5. Install packages.


Adhoc:
Only for single task.
Complex deployments or configurations don't use adhoc commands.

